In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with 1 cup sweetened condensed milk. Remove from heat; stir in nuts (optional) and vanilla. Spread evenly into wax-paper-lined 8- or 9-inch square pan. In clean heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt butterscotch chips and remaining sweetened condensed milk. Spread evenly over chocolate layer. Chill 3 hours or until firm. Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.